Class SequenceFeature

public class SequenceFeature
extends java.lang.Object
implements com.clarkparsia.empire.SupportsRdfId

The SBOL data model's Sequence Feature for RDF and Json. The objects of this type represent DNA features which describe DnaComponents found in the Library. They are associated with DnaComponents via the position and strand information found in the SequenceAnnotation. They SHOULD have a DnaSequence object which corresponds to the sequence of the DnaComponent starting and ending at the SequenceAnnotation position in the direction given by the strand. DnaComponents are EXPECTED to be found inside a SBOL Library object. TODO: SHOULD, EXPECTED above

Since:
0.1, 02/08/2011

mgaldzic

Returns:

setDescription

public void setDescription(java.lang.String description)
Text which is written for users to read and interpret. It should describe what the feature is used for and/or what it does. Suggestion: it should provide information that cannot yet be represented in the rest of the feature's computable fields. Do not include <> tags such as HTML or XML inside as that may break the RDF. Don't include {} tags as that may break the Json.

Parameters:
description - Human readable text describing the feature
